  "text": "These results show, for the first time to our knowledge, a procedure that eliminates the requirement for a lengthy sample incubation time in order to measure individual folate vitamers as monoglutamate folate. Previous research from our laboratory has shown that a 4-h incubation period in 1% ascorbic acid is required before HPLC-MS/MS analysis of folates as monoglutamates [CITATION_1] . In contrast, the microbiological assay responds to di-and triglutamate folates, requiring only a 30-min",
